                <h2>Latest</h2>        
                                            
                            <dl>
                                                           <dt><a href="http://www.webdesignfromscratch.com/web-design/top-10-best-designed-web-sites-in-the-world-2010/">Top 10 Best Designed Web Sites in the World (2010) (Dec 1 2010)</a></dt>
                               <dd>Ben Hunt presents his Top 10 Best Web Design examples of 2010, explaining why each site design is so effective.</dd>
                                                           <dt><a href="http://www.webdesignfromscratch.com/design-process/how-to-learn-web-design/">How To Learn Web Design (Nov 30 2010)</a></dt>
                               <dd>Ben Hunt's recommendations on the most important skills in web design and where to learn them.</dd>
                                                           <dt><a href="http://www.webdesignfromscratch.com/blog/why-wordpress-is-our-cms-of-choice/">Why WordPress is our CMS of Choice (Oct 22 2010)</a></dt>
                               <dd>A look at some of the WordPress features that make it a great content management system, allowing your clients to edit their sites with ease.</dd>
                                                           <dt><a href="http://www.webdesignfromscratch.com/blog/train-to-be-a-pro-web-designer/">I Will Train You to be a Pro Web Designer (Sep 7 2010)</a></dt>
                               <dd>Introducing Ben Hunt's new online course in professional web design. Learn all the skills to run your own business in web design.</dd>
                                                           <dt><a href="http://www.webdesignfromscratch.com/blog/me2solar-e-commerce-site-designed-by-scratchmedia/">Me2solar E-commerce Site Designed by Scratchmedia (Aug 18 2010)</a></dt>
                               <dd>UK-based Web Designers Scratchmedia recently delivered this new e-commerce site for US/German Me2Solar, makers of innovative portable solar chargers</dd>
                                                           <dt><a href="http://www.webdesignfromscratch.com/blog/gurushot-scratchmedias-latest-web2-0-application-design-project/">GuruShot &#8211; Scratchmedia&#8217;s Latest Web2.0 Application Design Project (Aug 16 2010)</a></dt>
                               <dd>Introducing GuruShot, a new Web2.0 web-based application. GuruShot is a wisdom sharing site designed and built by UK Web2.0 designers Scratchmedia.</dd>
                                                           <dt><a href="http://www.webdesignfromscratch.com/web-design/web-design-review-of-philosophersnotes-com/">Web Design Review of Philosophersnotes.com (Aug 2 2010)</a></dt>
                               <dd>Ben Hunt reviews one of his favourite web site designs of the moment, explains what works and why, and shows you how you can apply the techniques.</dd>
                                                           <dt><a href="http://www.webdesignfromscratch.com/basics/what-is-the-relationship-between-graphic-design-and-web-design/">What is the Relationship Between Graphic Design and Web Design? (Aug 1 2010)</a></dt>
                               <dd>Explores the difference between design, graphic design, and web design. Argues that web design is a much broader discipline than graphic design.</dd>
                                                           <dt><a href="http://www.webdesignfromscratch.com/blog/newsletter-april-2010/">Ben Hunt&#8217;s Web Design Newsletter, April 2010 (Apr 7 2010)</a></dt>
                               <dd>Ben Hunt's web design newsletter April 2010: Conversion Rate Optimization, 2 new Web2.0 projects, and a trip of a lifetime</dd>
                                                           <dt><a href="http://www.webdesignfromscratch.com/basics/make-better-web-sites-with-my-simple-step-by-step-guide/">Make Better Web Sites with My Easy Step-by-Step Guide (Mar 11 2010)</a></dt>
                               <dd>Ben Hunt's best-selling ebook, "Save the Pixel" is the perfect guide to web design for non-designers, showing how anyone can make a web site better.</dd>
                                                           <dt><a href="http://www.webdesignfromscratch.com/basics/how-you-can-easily-boost-your-web-sites-success/">How You Can Easily Boost Your Web Site&#8217;s Success Today. A Simple Step-by-Step Guide (Mar 11 2010)</a></dt>
                               <dd>How every web site owner can make their site more effective by applying the principles of simple web design explained in Ben Hunt's ebook</dd>
                                                           <dt><a href="http://www.webdesignfromscratch.com/blog/conversion-rate-optimisation-case-study-split-test/">Case Study: Increasing conversion rate using Google Website Optimizer (Feb 1 2010)</a></dt>
                               <dd>A case study on increasing conversion rate with split testing using Google Website Optimizer</dd>
                                                           <dt><a href="http://www.webdesignfromscratch.com/blog/blogging-for-business-seminar-dvd-prerelease/">Order Your Copy of the Blogging for Business Pre-Release DVD (Jan 28 2010)</a></dt>
                               <dd>Order your pre-release copy of Ben Hunt and Mark Attwood's "Blogging for Business" seminar</dd>
                                                           <dt><a href="http://www.webdesignfromscratch.com/basics/the-simple-shall-inherit-the-web/">The Simple Shall Inherit the World Wide Web (Jan 17 2010)</a></dt>
                               <dd>The case for simplicity in web design, with tips and guidance for designers</dd>
                                                           <dt><a href="http://www.webdesignfromscratch.com/blog/case-study-double-your-conversion-rate/">Conversion Rate Optimisation Case Study: Bible Timeline (Jan 8 2010)</a></dt>
                               <dd>How Scratchmedia's designers tripled one customer's web site's conversion rate</dd>
                                                        </dl>
                            
                <h2>Categories</h2>
                        <dl>
                           <dt><a href="http://www.webdesignfromscratch.com/basics/">Basics</a></dt>
                           <dd>Tutorials on all the  basic skills for web site design and designing good usable web pages, through insight into the core thinking that supports the design of effective and usable web sites.</dd>
                           <dt><a href="http://www.webdesignfromscratch.com/design-process/">Design process</a></dt>
                           <dd>Looks at the discipline of web design, how to approach design as a job, and introduces some mental techniques for increasing enjoyment and success.</dd>
                           <dt><a href="http://www.webdesignfromscratch.com/web-design/">Graphic Design</a></dt>
                           <dd> Tutorials on the core visual graphic design skills for designing web pages that are easy to understand and easy to use.</dd>
                           <dt><a href="http://www.webdesignfromscratch.com/business/">Business of web design</a></dt>
                           <dd>This section provides guidelines from our experience of running web teams and our own agency, which we hope will help you be more successful and more fulfilled.</dd>
                           <dt><a href="http://www.webdesignfromscratch.com/goal-oriented-design/">Goal-oriented design</a></dt>
                           <dd>Understanding goals is critical to creating successful web experiences. This section teaches simple techniques to help you discover your own goals and gain insight into what your target audience really wants.</dd>
                           <dt><a href="http://www.webdesignfromscratch.com/website-architecture/">Website architecture</a></dt>
                           <dd>Tips on organising your web site to be easy to browse.</dd>
                           <!--<dt><a href="http://www.webdesignfromscratch.com/accessibility/">Accessibility</a></dt>
                           <dd>How to make your web pages easily accessible to everyone, regardless of disability or other factors.</dd>-->
                           <dt><a href="http://www.webdesignfromscratch.com/usability/">Usability</a></dt>
                           <dd>A range of articles and case studies on the subject of making web sites easy to use.</dd>
                           <dt><a href="http://www.webdesignfromscratch.com/copywriting/">Copy writing</a></dt>
                           <dd>Insight into writing compelling and successful copy for the web.</dd>
                           <dt><a href="http://www.webdesignfromscratch.com/html-css/">HTML / CSS</a></dt>
                           <dd>Introduction to the main technologies used to produce web pages.</dd>
                           <dt><a href="http://www.webdesignfromscratch.com/javascript/">JavaScript</a></dt>
                           <dd>A few tutorials on Javascript, the scripting language used to make most web pages interactive.</dd>
                           <dt><a href="http://www.webdesignfromscratch.com/resources/">Resources</a></dt>
                           <dd>We recommend a range of resources to help you be a more effective designer or developer.</dd>
